main event: On January 13 and 14, 1961, several witnesses reported seeing two unidentified flying objects hovering over a field in Reardan, Washington.
interesting points: The objects were described as having unusual lights not resembling normal aircraft characteristics., The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes., Witnesses indicated that the lights were bright and made no sound., Investigators couldn't confirm the objects as any known aircraft or flares despite a thorough search., Multiple reliable witnesses, including military personnel, corroborated the sighting.
sighted object: two unidentified flying objects with bright lights
witness description: Local residents and military personnel observed the lights from a distance.
